        <p>German-born physician and botanist in South Africa. Studied medicine and botany at Leipzig before moving to Cape Town in 1831, initially practising as a doctor. First colonial botanist and South Africa’s first professor of botany, 1858. International government adviser on botanical issues.</p></note>
